Spec: Invoice Service

Platform: TypeScript/Node

Purpose:
  Coordinate invoice creation through an external billing provider.

Structure:
  src: Source code
  tests: Test suite

Owns:
  invoice.ts
  invoice.test.ts

Can modify:
  invoice.ts
  invoice.test.ts

Can read:
  ../models/*
  ../ports/*

References:
  ../models/invoice.sdd
  ../ports/billing-provider.sdd

Must:
  Validate input before provider calls.
  Persist invoice after provider success.
  Normalize provider errors before returning them.

Must not:
  Call Stripe directly.
  Calculate tax.
  Send emails.

Depends on:
  InvoiceRepository
  BillingCustomerRepository
  BillingProviderPort

Forbids:
  stripe

Exposes:
  InvoiceService.createInvoice(input)

Accepts:
  CreateInvoiceInput

Returns:
  InvoiceResult

Raises:
  InvalidInvoiceError
  BillingProviderError

Handles:
  provider timeout
  unsupported currency
  missing customer id

Tasks:
  [x] #1 Define createInvoice public method.
  [ ] #2 Add validation for unsupported currency.
  [!] #3 Decide whether provider timeout should retry automatically.
  [?] #4 Confirm whether draft invoices can be deleted.
  [-] #5 Skip PDF rendering; owned by invoice-pdf feature.

Scenario: invalid invoice amount
  Given an invoice input with amount less than or equal to zero
  When createInvoice is called
  Then the invoice is rejected
  And the billing provider is not called

Scenario: provider timeout
  Given the billing provider takes too long
  When createInvoice is called
  Then a BillingProviderError is raised

Example:
  POST /invoices { customerId: "c_123", amount: 100 }

Done when:
  All scenarios have tests.
  No forbidden dependencies are imported.
  Public contract is preserved.
